{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950", "id": 1169149350, "node_id": "I_kwDOAAsO6M5Fr82m", "number": 94950, "title": "Update safety requirements of `Vec::from_raw_parts`?", "user": {"login": "EFanZh", "id": 2160692, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxNjA2OTI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2160692?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh", "html_url": "https://github.com/EFanZh", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EFanZh/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2022-03-15T03:49:16Z", "updated_at": "2022-04-21T01:54:46Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "[The \u201cSafety\u201d section of the document of `Vec::from_raw_parts`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/vec/struct.Vec.html#safety) says:\r\n\r\n> - `length` needs to be less than or equal to `capacity`.\r\n> - `capacity` needs to be the capacity that the pointer was allocated with.\r\n\r\nI think the first requirement should also add \u201cThe first `length` elements starting from `ptr` are initialized\u201d. And the second requirement could be relaxed into \u201c`capacity` needs to be **less than or equal to** the capacity that the pointer was allocated with\u201d, this is because [`Allocator::deallocate`](`https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/alloc/trait.Allocator.html#tymethod.deallocate`) does not require specifying exact size that the pointer was allocated with.\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94950/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}